@DATABASE "Bomberman"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - B - Bomberman"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - B
                   ====================================

                                 Bomberman
                                 =========


DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Infinite Lives" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(33248,0)"}          33248,0
@{"Lives = x     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(32851,255)"}          32851,x (x= 1-255)
@{"Difficulty = x" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(32846,1)"}          32846,x (x= 1-255)


                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).

                         I haven't tested this one as I don't have the
                         game :(

                         Rastan
@endnode
